The SIAI S. 13 was a idrocaccia-reconnaissance biplane developed by the Italian company to Company Seaplanes Alta Italia (SIAI) in the late first decade of the TWENTIETH century.In addition to the Italian company, after the engineer Conflenti decided to move to the Chantiers Apartment-Maritimes de la Seine was produced under license and marketed as the CAMS C. 13, was also produced under license in Spain.Mainly used in the air component of the royal Navy, the navy of the Kingdom of Italy, after the end of the first world war, attended with a single-seater version converted to racing use, vincendola without approval, the challenged third edition of the Cup Schneider of 1919 .
